FROM (VALUES
  ('eb9bfe77-dc3f-5138-88c3-adaf3b1fdddb', 'RF-IM-006', 'IND_MFG_D12', 'MFG-ROLE-057', 'Practitioner Pharma Production, QA/QC and Validation - Validation Engineer works within industrial manufacturing by handling validation protocols, qualification evidence, deviation/CAPA links, and release-support documentation across GMP Production and Batch Documentation; QA/QC Validation and Release Support. The role owns day-to-day exception resolution and prepares release-ready evidence, using source-traceable production, quality, test, maintenance, validation or release records without taking final authority where regulated sign-off, customer acceptance, EHS/legal filing or senior release approval is required.', 'I', 'C', 'R', 'ICR', 'Practitioner Pharma Production, QA/QC and Validation - Validation Engineer is mapped to ICR because its industrial manufacturing environment involves validation protocols, qualification evidence, deviation/CAPA links, and release-support documentation. Investigative / Conventional / Realistic is relevant because the role uses physical process evidence, engineering judgement, quality documentation, test or batch records, and structured release controls while producing evidence such as BMR/BPR, cleanroom status, equipment line clearance, batch manufacturing record and SAP/QMS entry; line clearance record, validation protocol, deviation/CAPA, batch review, GMP documentation and lab result.', 'Practitioner Pharma Production, QA/QC and Validation - Validation Engineer owns day-to-day exception resolution and prepares release-ready evidence; checks validation protocols, qualification evidence, deviation/CAPA links, and release-support documentation against Pharma Production, QA/QC and Validation evidence requirements; reviews gmp production and batch documentation; qa/qc validation and release support records for missing source references, mismatched measurements, timing gaps, route deviations, quality holds, safety constraints, test failures, validation gaps or unresolved handoff items; updates the applicable traveler, route sheet, BMR/BPR, FAT file, inspection report, ESD log, DCS/shift record, NCR/CAPA note or release tracker; proves the behaviour through BMR/BPR, cleanroom status, equipment line clearance, batch manufacturing record and SAP/QMS entry; line clearance record, validation protocol, deviation/CAPA, batch review, GMP documentation and lab result.', 'Practitioner Pharma Production, QA/QC and Validation - Validation Engineer works in Pharma Production, QA/QC and Validation within Industrial Manufacturing. The role context is GMP Production and Batch Documentation; QA/QC Validation and Release Support; its work is evidenced through BMR/BPR, cleanroom status, equipment line clearance, batch manufacturing record and SAP/QMS entry; line clearance record, validation protocol, deviation/CAPA, batch review, GMP documentation and lab result. The role mainly deals with validation protocols, qualification evidence, deviation/CAPA links, and release-support documentation and remains inside support, engineering execution, quality review, release preparation, maintenance coordination, validation support or documentation-control boundaries.', 'Practitioner Pharma Production, QA/QC and Validation - Validation Engineer: owns day-to-day exception resolution and prepares release-ready evidence; checks validation protocols, qualification evidence, deviation/CAPA links, and release-support documentation; reviews role inputs and exceptions in Pharma Production, QA/QC and Validation; updates the relevant route sheet, traveler, checklist, inspection record, test file, shift log, BMR/BPR, NCR/CAPA or dispatch/release tracker; prepares evidence from BMR/BPR, cleanroom status, equipment line clearance, batch manufacturing record and SAP/QMS entry; line clearance record, validation protocol, deviation/CAPA, batch review, GMP documentation and lab result; escalates items needing senior approval, QA release, customer approval, EHS/legal sign-off, regulated validation or cross-functional decision ownership.', 'Practitioner Pharma Production, QA/QC and Validation - Validation Engineer output evidence includes: Practitioner Pharma Production, QA/QC and Validation - Validation Engineer evidence pack using BMR/BPR, cleanroom status, equipment line clearance, batch manufacturing record and SAP/QMS entry; line clearance record, validation protocol, deviation/CAPA, batch review, GMP documentation and lab result; Practitioner Pharma Production, QA/QC and Validation - Validation Engineer issue/action note with source record, owner, date, status, blocker and escalation need; Practitioner Pharma Production, QA/QC and Validation - Validation Engineer closure evidence pack with checklist, supporting record, decision-boundary note and reviewer or owner sign-off.', '{"numerical_reasoning": 74.0, "logical_reasoning": 89.0, "verbal_reasoning": 70.0, "spatial_reasoning": 66.0, "data_interpretation": 88.0, "pattern_recognition": 86.0}'::jsonb, '{"openness": 4.0, "extraversion": 3.0, "agreeableness": 4.0, "conscientiousness": 5.0, "emotional_stability": 4.0}'::jsonb, '{"impact": 5.0, "status": 3.0, "autonomy": 3.0, "security": 5.0, "financial": 4.0, "lifestyle": 3.0, "creativity": 3.0, "leadership": 3.0}'::jsonb, '{"areas": ["Logical Reasoning", "Data Interpretation", "Pattern Recognition"], "rationale": "Practitioner Pharma Production, QA/QC and Validation - Validation Engineer depends most on logical reasoning, data interpretation, pattern recognition because the work involves reading technical records, comparing measurements or trends, interpreting defects, tracing source evidence and deciding the correct containment, release, rework or escalation route. Lower readiness in mandatory areas should trigger bridge practice rather than automatic rejection unless the role is safety, license, GMP, aerospace/defence or authority gated."}'::jsonb, '{"traits": ["Conscientiousness", "Openness", "Agreeableness"], "rationale": "Practitioner Pharma Production, QA/QC and Validation - Validation Engineer benefits from conscientiousness, openness, agreeableness because the role requires disciplined evidence handling, careful exception tracking, stable follow-through and communication across production, quality, engineering, maintenance, supplier, lab or customer owners. These traits should adjust confidence and coaching focus, not act as a hard exclusion rule."}'::jsonb, '{"values": ["Impact", "Security", "Financial Growth"], "rationale": "Practitioner Pharma Production, QA/QC and Validation - Validation Engineer aligns best with learners who value impact, security, financial growth because the role environment involves visible manufacturing output, stable operating discipline, accountable quality outcomes and ownership of closure evidence. Work values should be used to prioritise role options, not to prove technical ability."}'::jsonb, 'Preferred', 'B.Pharm; M.Pharm; B.Sc Chemistry; Microbiology; Biotechnology; Mechanical; Electrical; Instrumentation', true),
