  ('398f6415-812d-5198-a0dd-be9d427cc051', 'TLS-RF-001', 'IND_TLS_D01', 'TLS-ROLE-001', 'Transport Dispatcher works within road freight dispatch & transport operations for the transportation, logistics and supply-chain industry. The role handles vehicle placement, trip sheets, route readiness, e-way bill checks, GPS milestone tracking and dispatch exception closure across Freight Trip Dispatch & Route Execution, using evidence such as truck consignments, route plans, trip sheets, e-way bills, PODs without crossing final customs, carrier, QA, customer-commercial, safety, regulatory or senior approval authority.', 'R', 'C', 'E', 'RCE', 'Transport Dispatcher is mapped to RCE because its logistics environment involves vehicle placement, trip sheets, route readiness, e-way bill checks, GPS milestone tracking and dispatch exception closure. Realistic / Conventional / Enterprising is relevant because the role combines movement coordination, documentation discipline, exception follow-up, customer/vendor interaction and evidence-backed operational closure using truck consignments, route plans, trip sheets, e-way bills, PODs.', 'Transport Dispatcher checks vehicle placement, trip sheets, route readiness, e-way bill checks, GPS milestone tracking and dispatch exception closure against Road Freight Dispatch & Transport Operations requirements; notices missing documents, mismatched milestones, route or capacity gaps, SLA risks, temperature or compliance exceptions, customer remarks, vendor non-response or unresolved handoff items; updates the relevant TMS/WMS/TOS/ERP/control-tower tracker, gate record, AWB packet, POD file, dispatch manifest, route plan, logger record or exception note; proves the behaviour through truck consignments, route plans, trip sheets, e-way bills, PODs.', 'Transport Dispatcher works in Road Freight Dispatch & Transport Operations within Transportation, Logistics & Supply Chain. The role context is Freight Trip Dispatch & Route Execution; its work is evidenced through truck consignments, route plans, trip sheets, e-way bills, PODs. The role mainly deals with vehicle placement, trip sheets, route readiness, e-way bill checks, GPS milestone tracking and dispatch exception closure and remains inside coordination, documentation, execution support, exception handling, analytics support, customer/vendor follow-up or release-preparation boundaries.', 'Transport Dispatcher: checks vehicle placement, trip sheets, route readiness, e-way bill checks, GPS milestone tracking and dispatch exception closure; reviews role inputs and exceptions in Road Freight Dispatch & Transport Operations; updates the relevant route sheet, trip sheet, POD file, gate record, yard plan, booking tracker, AWB packet, WMS task, dispatch manifest, logger record, vendor SLA log or optimization note; prepares evidence from truck consignments, route plans, trip sheets, e-way bills, PODs; escalates items needing customs approval, QA/GDP release, carrier confirmation, safety clearance, customer-commercial approval, regulatory decision or senior operations ownership.', 'Transport Dispatcher output evidence includes: Transport Dispatcher evidence pack using truck consignments, route plans, trip sheets, e-way bills, PODs; Transport Dispatcher issue/action note with source record, owner, date, status, blocker and escalation need; Transport Dispatcher closure evidence pack with checklist, supporting record, decision-boundary note and reviewer or owner sign-off.', '{"numerical_reasoning": 64.0, "logical_reasoning": 70.0, "verbal_reasoning": 64.0, "spatial_reasoning": 60.0, "data_interpretation": 76.0, "pattern_recognition": 72.0}'::jsonb, '{"openness": 3.0, "extraversion": 3.0, "agreeableness": 4.0, "conscientiousness": 5.0, "emotional_stability": 4.0}'::jsonb, '{"impact": 5.0, "status": 3.0, "autonomy": 3.0, "security": 5.0, "financial": 4.0, "lifestyle": 3.0, "creativity": 2.0, "leadership": 4.0}'::jsonb, '{"areas": ["Data Interpretation", "Pattern Recognition